Read Me Notes

On the Pi zero you will need to make a service that starts the Webserver as soon as it boots and restarts if it craches. Use the following:

Create a file /etc/systemd/system/Webserver.service

[Unit]
Description=Webserver service that starts service
After=network.target
StartLimitIntervalSec=0
[Service]
Type=simple
Restart=always
RestartSec=1
User=pi
ExecStart=/usr/bin/python3 /user/home/pi/Desktop/Webserver.py

[Install]
WantedBy=multi-user.target


save file and then run: systemctl start Webserver
Then follow this up with this command to start on boot: systemctl enable Webserver
